SIMPLE: rorqual
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rorqual
<hw>Ror"qual</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Norw.
<ets>rorqualus</ets> a whale with folds.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A very large North Atlantic whalebone whale (<spn>Physalus
antiquorum</spn>, or <spn>Balaenoptera physalus</spn>). It has a dorsal
fin, and strong longitudinal folds on the throat and belly. Called also
<altname>razorback</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ It is one of the largest of the whales, somethimes
becoming nearly one hundred feet long, but it is more slender than the
right whales, and is noted for its swiftness. The name is sometimes
applied to other related species of finback whales.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rorulent</ent>⟦br⟧
